5. Reuse existing schema definitions wherever possible. Do not duplicate schemas unless absolutely necessary.
6. Follow the project's existing OpenAPI conventions, formatting, indentation, naming standards, tags, operationId, responses, and reusable components.
7. Add the new API path to the appropriate YAML file.
8. If required, add any new request or response schemas under components while minimizing duplication.
9. Do not modify the existing DynamicScreen API.
10. Ensure the OpenAPI specification is valid and builds successfully.

Deliverables:
- Show all modified YAML files.
- Explain any newly added schemas or references.
- Reuse existing definitions wherever possible.
